      "content": "the hooded figures idea is interesting. i want to make sure i'm not just being generic though. i want the dread to come from the specific \"essence\" of this kind of place. \n\nwhen you mention the \"malevolence\" in the air or the \"vibe\" of a neighborhood like this, do you think that darkness is tied to the people living there, or just the environment itself? like, in a way that makes the residents part of the \"horror\" or the reason why a stranger would feel so instinctively unsafe? i want to understand how to write that tension between the community and the fear of the unknown.",
      "source": "evaluator"
